The rational Bézier curve adds adjustable weights to provide closer approximations to arbitrary shapes. The numerator is a weighted Bernstein-form Bézier curve and the denominator is a weighted sum of <a href="Bernstein%20polynomial">Bernstein polynomial</a>s. Rational Bézier curves can, among other uses, be used to represent segments of <a href="conic%20section">conic section</a>s exactly, including circular arcs.

